=== Introduction ===

CalcPHP is a math expression calculator write in PHP. 

I write it just for fun and for programming language parsing and compiling study purpose.

You can use it as a command line tool like :

    # php CalcPHP.php
    CalcPHP command line interface V1.0
    > 1.
    result: 1.000000 (0.000102 sec)
    > 1 + 2.
    result: 3.000000 (0.000133 sec)
    > 1 + 2 * 3.
    result: 7.000000 (0.000426 sec)
    > 1 + 2 * 3 / 4.
    result: 2.500000 (0.000357 sec)
    > (1 + 2) * (3 / 4).
    result: 2.250000 (0.000329 sec)
    > a = 1, b = 2, c = 3, (a + b) / c.
    result: 1.000000 (0.000782 sec)
    > exit

And you can embed the "CalcPHP Language" in your app by include "CalcPHP.php", and use it like:

    //create global state
    $state = new CalcState();

    //create a parser
    $parser = new CalcParser($code);

    //parse one statement
    $explist = $parser->ParseSta();

    //get the last expression's result
    foreach ($explist as $exp) {
        $result = $exp->Exec($state);
    }


=== Syntax ===

The CalcPHP command line interface execute "CalcPHP Language" statement by read line.

The statement end with '.' and include one or more expression, expressions split by ','.

The statement's value equals the last expression's value in this statement.

Example 1:

    CalcPHP command line interface V1.0
    > 1.
    result: 1.000000 (0.000142 sec)
    > 1, 2.
    result: 2.000000 (0.000138 sec)

A variable named in "[_a-zA-Z][_0-9a-zA-Z]*" format and default value is 0.

Example 2:

    CalcPHP command line interface V1.0
    > a.
    result: 0.000000 (0.000164 sec)
    > a = 1.
    result: 1.000000 (0.000181 sec)
    > b = a + 1.
    result: 2.000000 (0.000216 sec)

